### GET /api/auth/token

Source: https://www.better-auth.com/llms.txt/docs/plugins/jwt

Retrieves a JWT token for the authenticated user. This endpoint returns a JWT token that can be used to authenticate requests to external services. The token is included in the response and should be used in the Authorization header as a Bearer token.

```APIDOC
## GET /api/auth/token

### Description
Retrieves a JWT token for the authenticated user. This endpoint returns a JWT token that can be used to authenticate requests to external services and APIs that require JWT authentication.

### Method
GET

### Endpoint
/api/auth/token

### Parameters
#### Headers
- **Authorization** (string) - Required - Bearer token or session token for authentication

### Request Example
```
GET /api/auth/token
Headers: {
  "Authorization": "Bearer {session_token}"
}
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **token** (string) - The JWT token that can be used for authenticated requests to external services

#### Response Example
```json
{
  "token": "REDACTED"
}
```

### Usage
Include the returned token in the Authorization header of requests to external services:
```
Authorization: Bearer {token}
```
```

--------------------------------

### JWT Token Response Format

Source: https://www.better-auth.com/llms.txt/docs/plugins/jwt

The JSON structure returned by the Better-Auth token endpoint.

```json
{
  "token": "ey..."
}
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Callback for Existing User Sign-Up Attempts in better-auth (auth.ts)

Source: https://www.better-auth.com/llms.txt/docs/authentication/email-password

This snippet illustrates how to use the `onExistingUserSignUp` callback within `better-auth` to notify an existing user when someone attempts to register with their email address. This helps prevent user enumeration by returning a success response while informing the legitimate user of potential activity.

```ts
import { betterAuth } from "better-auth";
import { sendEmail } from "./email"; // your email sending function

export const auth = betterAuth({
  emailAndPassword: {
    enabled: true,
    requireEmailVerification: true,
    onExistingUserSignUp: async ({ user }, request) => {
      void sendEmail({
        to: user.email,
        subject: "Sign-up attempt with your email",
        text: "Someone tried to create an account using your email address. If this was you, try signing in instead. If not, you can safely ignore this email.",
      });
    },
  },
});
```

--------------------------------

### Define SendEmailResult Response Interface

Source: https://www.better-auth.com/llms.txt/docs/infrastructure/services/email

Defines the response format returned by the sendEmail function. Includes success status, optional message ID from the email provider, and optional error message if the send operation failed.

```typescript
interface SendEmailResult {
  success: boolean;
  messageId?: string;
  error?: string;
}
```

